==English==

===Etymology===
From [[truce]] (notably the 1853 Perpetual Maritime Truce) + [[-ial]] + [[states]] (the plural of [[state]]).

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|-}}

# {{former name of|Trucial Oman|lang=en}} The precursor of the [[United Arab Emirates]] (UAE), comprising most of the small Arab coastal states (then [[sheikhdom]]s) located along the [[Persian Gulf]], which were Bitish [[protectorate]]s since the 1820 General Maritime Treaty.

